00:00:03,629 --> 00:00:06,298
[ HUMMING ]

2
00:00:06,340 --> 00:00:08,383
GOOD MORNING, EVERYONE.

3
00:00:08,425 --> 00:00:11,470
[ HUMMING CONTINUES ]

4
00:00:14,097 --> 00:00:15,850
[ CHIRPING AND FLUTTERING ]

5
00:00:15,891 --> 00:00:17,852
[ CHUCKLES ]

6
00:00:17,893 --> 00:00:20,855
BE PATIENT.

7
00:00:20,896 --> 00:00:22,857
[ RUSTLING ]

8
00:00:22,898 --> 00:00:24,023
[ GROANS ]

9
00:00:24,065 --> 00:00:26,694
AH AH AH AH!

10
00:00:33,659 --> 00:00:36,328
[ CHUCKLES ]

11
00:00:36,370 --> 00:00:37,830
AHH.

12
00:00:38,914 --> 00:00:41,333
SOMEONE HAD A BUSY NIGHT.

13
00:00:48,966 --> 00:00:50,634
DON'T WORRY.

14
00:00:50,676 --> 00:00:52,803
[ CHIRPING ]

15
00:00:52,845 --> 00:00:54,680
I DIDN'T FORGET YOU.

16
00:00:58,893 --> 00:01:00,936
NOW...

17
00:01:03,898 --> 00:01:07,526
LET'S TRY IT WITHOUT BITING
MY FINGERS THIS TIME, HMM?

18
00:01:07,568 --> 00:01:09,319
[ CHIRPING ]

19
00:01:22,416 --> 00:01:27,004
MAN: ♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

20
00:01:27,046 --> 00:01:30,257
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

21
00:01:30,298 --> 00:01:34,093
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

22
00:01:34,135 --> 00:01:37,806
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

23
00:01:37,848 --> 00:01:42,185
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

24
00:01:42,227 --> 00:01:45,814
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

25
00:01:45,856 --> 00:01:49,777
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

26
00:01:49,818 --> 00:01:52,780
♪ NO, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND ♪

27
00:01:52,821 --> 00:01:55,866
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

28
00:01:55,908 --> 00:01:57,826
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

29
00:01:57,868 --> 00:02:00,996
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

30
00:02:01,038 --> 00:02:05,876
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

31
00:02:05,918 --> 00:02:08,211
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

32
00:02:08,253 --> 00:02:13,092
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

33
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:16,053
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

34
00:02:16,095 --> 00:02:21,892
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

35
00:02:21,934 --> 00:02:23,560
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

36
00:02:23,602 --> 00:02:25,896
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

37
00:02:25,938 --> 00:02:29,566
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

38
00:02:29,608 --> 00:02:34,113
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

39
00:02:46,041 --> 00:02:49,003
HOSHI: PEOPLE ARE
GETTING JEALOUS.

40
00:02:49,044 --> 00:02:51,046
YOU GET MORE
LETTERS FROM HOME

41
00:02:51,088 --> 00:02:52,965
THAN ANYONE ON THIS SHIP.

42
00:02:53,007 --> 00:02:55,342
WHAT'S HER NAME?

43
00:02:55,383 --> 00:02:56,760
[ CHUCKLES ]
IT'S NOTHING LIKE THAT.

44
00:02:56,802 --> 00:02:58,303
THEY'RE FROM DR. LUCAS.
HE'S A COLLEAGUE

45
00:02:58,345 --> 00:03:00,305
FROM THE INTERSPECIES
MEDICAL EXCHANGE.

46
00:03:00,347 --> 00:03:02,557
I DIDN'T KNOW THERE WERE
HUMANS SERVING ON DENOBULA.

47
00:03:02,599 --> 00:03:04,183
HE'S THE FIRST.

48
00:03:04,225 --> 00:03:05,978
HE HELPED ME GET SETTLED IN
WHEN I CAME TO SAN FRANCISCO.

49
00:03:06,020 --> 00:03:08,105
I'M TRYING
TO RETURN THE FAVOR.

50
00:03:08,147 --> 00:03:10,482
HOSHI: I HAD A PEN PAL ONCE,
WHEN I WAS 12,

51
00:03:10,524 --> 00:03:12,067
FROM BRISBANE, AUSTRALIA.

52
00:03:12,109 --> 00:03:14,402
I LOVED GETTING HER LETTERS.

53
00:03:14,444 --> 00:03:15,988
IT WAS LIKE THIS LITTLE WINDOW

54
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:19,533
INTO DISTANT PLACES
WITH STRANGE-SOUNDING NAMES.

55
00:03:19,574 --> 00:03:22,703
THE CURIOSITY
OF AN EXPLORER, EVEN THEN.

56
00:03:22,744 --> 00:03:24,079
ARE WE STILL ON FOR LATER?

57
00:03:24,121 --> 00:03:25,706
OH, YES.

58
00:03:25,747 --> 00:03:27,624
I'M LOOKING FORWARD TO IT.

59
00:03:27,666 --> 00:03:31,210
IF YOU THINK YOU'RE READY,
WE CAN TACKLE GERUNDS TODAY.

60
00:03:31,252 --> 00:03:33,296
I CAN HARDLY WAIT.

61
00:03:37,968 --> 00:03:39,553
[ BEEP ]

62
00:03:39,594 --> 00:03:43,306
MAN:<i> MY DEAR DR. PHLOX,</i>
<i>IT'S ME AGAIN--JEREMY.</i>

63
00:03:43,348 --> 00:03:44,558
<i>I HOPE YOU ARE WELL.</i>

64
00:03:44,599 --> 00:03:46,601
<i>IT'S BEEN</i>
<i>A HELL OF A WEEK HERE --</i>

65
00:03:46,643 --> 00:03:49,563
<i>WALL-TO-WALL EMERGENCIES</i>
<i>AND THREE MIDNIGHT DELIVERIES.</i>

66
00:03:49,604 --> 00:03:51,940
<i>IT'S MATING SEASON,</i>
<i>SO YOU KNOW HOW THAT GOES.</i>

67
00:03:51,982 --> 00:03:53,984
<i>I THOUGHT HUMAN REPRODUCTION</i>
<i>WAS COMPLICATED.</i>

68
00:03:54,026 --> 00:03:58,989
<i>YOU DENOBULANS MAKE US LOOK</i>
<i>LIKE SINGLE-CELL ORGANISMS.</i>

69
00:04:02,367 --> 00:04:03,869
PHLOX:<i> DEAR DR. LUCAS,</i>

70
00:04:03,911 --> 00:04:05,954
<i>SORRY TO HEAR ABOUT</i>
<i>YOUR DIFFICULT WEEK.</i>

71
00:04:05,996 --> 00:04:08,707
<i>I KNOW THE RIGORS</i>
<i>OF MATING SEASON ONLY TOO WELL.</i>

72
00:04:08,749 --> 00:04:10,458
<i>IT MIGHT HELP TO BEAR IN MIND</i>

73
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:13,253
<i>THAT A DOSE OF NIAXILIN</i>
<i>CAN BE QUITE EFFECTIVE</i>

74
00:04:13,294 --> 00:04:15,589
<i>IN SEPARATING THE TWO...</i>
<i>COMBATANTS.</i>

75
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:17,966
<i>IT SOUNDS LIKE YOU'VE SETTLED</i>
<i>INTO YOUR NEW LIVING QUARTERS.</i>

76
00:04:18,008 --> 00:04:21,220
<i>THAT PART OF THE CITY HAS</i>
<i>SOME VERY LIVELY KAYBIN BARS</i>

77
00:04:21,261 --> 00:04:22,888
<i>ALONG THE RIVER.</i>

78
00:04:22,930 --> 00:04:24,556
TUCKER: UP HERE, DOC!

79
00:04:24,598 --> 00:04:26,892
PHLOX:<i> THEY'RE OPEN ALL NIGHT,</i>
<i>IF I RECALL.</i>

80
00:04:26,934 --> 00:04:28,977
<i>PLEASE, DON'T VENTURE</i>
<i>INSIDE THEM UNESCORTED.</i>

81
00:04:29,019 --> 00:04:32,606
<i>THEY CAN BE QUITE DISTURBING</i>
<i>TO THE UNINITIATED.</i>

82
00:04:32,647 --> 00:04:34,524
HE WAS TRYING TO REROUTE
A NITROGEN VALVE,

83
00:04:34,566 --> 00:04:36,110
AND THE SEAL BLEW.

84
00:04:36,151 --> 00:04:39,487
TUCKER: HOW BAD IS IT?

85
00:04:43,575 --> 00:04:45,577
OH, IT'S SUPERFICIAL.

86
00:04:45,619 --> 00:04:47,704
ONLY FIRST-DEGREE BURNS.

87
00:04:47,746 --> 00:04:51,374
A LITTLE DERMALINE GEL
SHOULD DO THE TRICK.

88
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:54,002
PHLOX:<i> MOST OF MY WORK</i>
<i>IS FAIRLY ROUTINE --</i>

89
00:04:54,044 --> 00:04:56,964
<i>SCRAPES AND BRUISES,</i>
<i>THE OCCASIONAL EMERGENCY.</i>

90
00:04:57,005 --> 00:04:59,007
<i>AND YOU'LL BE PLEASED TO HEAR</i>
<i>THAT THE CREW</i>

91
00:04:59,049 --> 00:05:00,968
<i>FINALLY SEEMS TO BE</i>
<i>GROWING ACCUSTOMED</i>

92
00:05:01,009 --> 00:05:02,552
<i>TO AN ALIEN DOCTOR ON BOARD.</i>

93
00:05:02,594 --> 00:05:05,013
<i>I MUST ADMIT, I WASN'T PLANNING</i>
<i>TO STAY THIS LONG,</i>

94
00:05:05,055 --> 00:05:07,266
<i>BUT THE OPPORTUNITY TO OBSERVE</i>
<i>YOUR SPECIES</i>

95
00:05:07,307 --> 00:05:09,268
<i>ON THEIR FIRST</i>
<i>DEEP-SPACE VENTURE</i>

96
00:05:09,309 --> 00:05:10,769
<i>HAS PROVEN IRRESISTIBLE.</i>

97
00:05:10,811 --> 00:05:12,146
LIEUTENANT.

98
00:05:12,187 --> 00:05:14,106
I SAVED A SEAT FOR YOU.

99
00:05:14,148 --> 00:05:15,816
AHH. ANOTHER TIME, DOCTOR.

100
00:05:15,857 --> 00:05:19,111
I'M DUE BACK IN THE ARMORY.

101
00:05:19,153 --> 00:05:21,029
<i>IT'S A BIT DAUNTING AT TIMES,</i>

102
00:05:21,071 --> 00:05:24,449
PHLOX:<i> TRYING TO SOCIALIZE WITH</i>
<i>THE CREW, FORM FRIENDSHIPS,</i>

103
00:05:24,491 --> 00:05:26,493
<i>BUT OUR PROFESSION GUARANTEES</i>

104
00:05:26,534 --> 00:05:29,037
<i>THAT SOONER OR LATER,</i>
<i>EVERYONE COMES TO SEE US.</i>

105
00:05:29,079 --> 00:05:31,790
<i>IT MAKES INTERACTION</i>
<i>QUITE A BIT EASIER.</i>

106
00:05:31,832 --> 00:05:36,170
IT'S JUST A LITTLE
GASTROINTESTINAL DISTRESS.

107
00:05:38,172 --> 00:05:40,674
HE HASN'T BEEN HIMSELF LATELY.

108
00:05:40,715 --> 00:05:44,761
WELL, YOU'VE BEEN FEEDING HIM
CHEESE AGAIN, HAVEN'T YOU?

109
00:05:44,803 --> 00:05:47,388
YOU'VE GOT TO LEARN
HOW TO SAY NO, CAPTAIN.

110
00:05:47,430 --> 00:05:49,183
NO MORE DAIRY PRODUCTS,
YOU HEAR THAT?

111
00:05:49,224 --> 00:05:50,684
DOCTOR'S ORDERS.

112
00:05:50,725 --> 00:05:52,393
PHLOX:<i> I NEVER THOUGHT</i>
<i>I'D MEET A SPECIES</i>

113
00:05:52,435 --> 00:05:55,480
THAT FORGES SUCH INTIMATE BONDS
<i>WITH LESSER CREATURES.</i>

114
00:05:55,522 --> 00:05:57,065
<i>IT'S SURPRISING, THE THINGS</i>

115
00:05:57,107 --> 00:06:00,027
<i>YOU HUMANS CHOOSE TO INVEST</i>
<i>YOUR EMOTIONS IN.</i>

116
00:06:00,068 --> 00:06:01,278
[ SIGHS ]

117
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:02,821
SORRY TO BOTHER YOU WITH THIS.

118
00:06:02,863 --> 00:06:04,281
NO BOTHER.

119
00:06:04,323 --> 00:06:06,449
HE WAS ONE OF MY MORE
COOPERATIVE PATIENTS TODAY.

120
00:06:06,491 --> 00:06:09,911
THANKS, DOC. [ SIGHS ]

121
00:06:09,953 --> 00:06:13,332
SEE ALL THE TROUBLE YOU CAUSE?

122
00:06:13,372 --> 00:06:14,708
PHLOX:<i> I'VE NOTICED HOW</i>
<i>THE CAPTAIN</i>

123
00:06:14,749 --> 00:06:16,126
<i>SEEMS TO ANTHROPOMORPHIZE</i>
<i>HIS PET.</i>

124
00:06:16,168 --> 00:06:18,003
<i>HE EVEN TALKS TO THE CREATURE,</i>

125
00:06:18,045 --> 00:06:21,756
<i>ALTHOUGH I'M FAIRLY CERTAIN IT</i>
<i>HAS NO IDEA WHAT HE'S SAYING.</i>

126
00:06:21,798 --> 00:06:23,424
<i>THEN AGAIN, I'VE BEEN KNOWN</i>

127
00:06:23,466 --> 00:06:26,928
<i>TO SPEAK TO MY PYRITHIAN BAT</i>
<i>ON OCCASION.</i>

128
00:06:26,970 --> 00:06:28,930
ROBERT:<i> WE WON'T BE GOING</i>
<i>TO AMERICA THIS TIME,</i>

129
00:06:28,972 --> 00:06:33,185
<i>BUT ALWAYS, I GO WITH YOU</i>
<i>WHEREVER YOU GO, UNDERSTAND?</i>

130
00:06:33,227 --> 00:06:35,103
<i>YOU GO NOW, MARIA.</i>

131
00:06:35,145 --> 00:06:37,272
MARIA:<i> NO -- NO,</i>
<i>I STAY WITH YOU, ROBERTO.</i>

132
00:06:37,314 --> 00:06:39,191
ROBERT:<i> NO, MARIA.</i>

133
00:06:39,233 --> 00:06:40,483
<i>WHAT I DO NOW, I DO ALONE.</i>

134
00:06:40,525 --> 00:06:42,652
<i>I COULDN'T DO IT</i>
<i>IF YOU WERE HERE.</i>

135
00:06:42,694 --> 00:06:44,779
<i>IF YOU GO, THEN I GO, TOO.</i>

136
00:06:44,821 --> 00:06:46,281
<i>DON'T YOU SEE HOW IT IS?</i>

137
00:06:46,323 --> 00:06:47,991
<i>WHICHEVER ONE THERE IS...</i>

138
00:06:48,033 --> 00:06:49,201
MARIA:<i> NO! NO...</i>

139
00:06:49,243 --> 00:06:50,827
CUTLER: WE CAN GO,
IF YOU'RE BORED.

140
00:06:50,869 --> 00:06:52,996
PHLOX: NO, NO. I'D LIKE TO STAY
AND SEE WHAT HAPPENS.

141
00:06:53,038 --> 00:06:54,206
WOMAN: SHH!

142
00:06:54,248 --> 00:06:57,334
CUTLER: YOU WON'T BE
DISAPPOINTED.

143
00:06:57,376 --> 00:06:59,253
THE ENDING'S CLASSIC.

144
00:06:59,294 --> 00:07:01,171
[ Chuckling ] NO, NOT THE FILM.

145
00:07:01,213 --> 00:07:04,507
I'M SENSING A RISING EMOTIONAL
UNDERCURRENT IN THE ROOM.

146
00:07:04,549 --> 00:07:06,260
I'M CURIOUS TO SEE
IF IT CULMINATES

147
00:07:06,301 --> 00:07:08,178
IN SOME KIND OF GROUP RESPONSE.

148
00:07:08,220 --> 00:07:11,514
CUTLER: THEY DON'T HAVE MOVIES
WHERE YOU COME FROM, DO THEY?

149
00:07:11,556 --> 00:07:13,641
WE HAD SOMETHING SIMILAR
A FEW HUNDRED YEARS AGO,

150
00:07:13,683 --> 00:07:15,936
BUT THEY LOST THEIR APPEAL
WHEN PEOPLE DISCOVERED

151
00:07:15,977 --> 00:07:18,146
THEIR REAL LIVES
WERE MORE INTERESTING.

152
00:07:18,188 --> 00:07:19,898
ROBERT:<i> IF YOU GO,</i>
<i>I GO, TOO.</i>

153
00:07:19,940 --> 00:07:23,026
WELL, STILL, IT'S NICE
TO TAKE A BREAK FROM YOUR LIFE

154
00:07:23,068 --> 00:07:25,153
EVERY NOW AND THEN,
DON'T YOU THINK?

155
00:07:25,195 --> 00:07:27,072
I SUPPOSE IT IS.

156
00:07:27,114 --> 00:07:29,283
[ POPCORN SHAKES ]

157
00:07:29,324 --> 00:07:30,617
OH.

158
00:07:30,658 --> 00:07:32,286
ROBERT:<i> AND IT'LL NEVER END.</i>

159
00:07:32,327 --> 00:07:33,620
MARIA: NO!

160
00:07:33,661 --> 00:07:36,081
ROBERT:<i> YOU'RE ME NOW,</i>
<i>AND I AM YOU.</i>

161
00:07:36,123 --> 00:07:37,249
[ CRUNCHING ]

162
00:07:37,291 --> 00:07:38,541
<i>NOW YOU UNDERSTAND.</i>

163
00:07:38,583 --> 00:07:40,210
[ SNIFFLES ]

164
00:07:40,252 --> 00:07:42,337
<i>NOW YOU'RE GOING...</i>

165
00:07:42,379 --> 00:07:44,298
[ SIGHS ]

166
00:07:44,339 --> 00:07:46,383
UH, SOMETHING IN MY EYE.

167
00:07:46,425 --> 00:07:49,094
ROBERT:<i> STAND UP NOW AND GO,</i>
<i>AND WE BOTH GO.</i>

168
00:07:49,136 --> 00:07:50,137
<i>STAND UP, MARIA.</i>

169
00:07:50,178 --> 00:07:51,221
[ CHUCKLES ]

170
00:07:51,263 --> 00:07:52,639
<i>REMEMBER, YOU'RE ME, TOO.</i>

171
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:54,266
PHLOX:<i> IT'S REMARKABLE, DOCTOR.</i>

172
00:07:54,308 --> 00:07:56,059
<i>EVEN FICTIONAL CHARACTERS</i>

173
00:07:56,101 --> 00:07:57,811
<i>SEEM TO ELICIT</i>
<i>HUMAN COMPASSION.</i>

174
00:07:57,852 --> 00:08:00,314
<i>MY SHIPMATES HAVE CALMLY FACED</i>
<i>ANY NUMBER OF DANGERS,</i>

175
00:08:00,355 --> 00:08:05,235
<i>AND YET A SIMPLE MOVIE</i>
<i>CAN BRING TEARS TO THEIR EYES.</i>

176
00:08:05,277 --> 00:08:09,072
[ MUSIC SWELLS ]

177
00:08:09,114 --> 00:08:10,615
PHLOX: TEMPORAL VEIN.

178
00:08:10,657 --> 00:08:12,117
CUTLER: TEMPORAL VEIN.

179
00:08:12,159 --> 00:08:14,119
INTERNAL MAXILLARY.

180
00:08:14,161 --> 00:08:17,331
AND WHAT IS THE MAXILLARY
CONNECTED TO?

181
00:08:17,372 --> 00:08:21,251
UH, POSTERIOR...AURICULAR?

182
00:08:21,293 --> 00:08:22,336
VERY GOOD.

183
00:08:22,377 --> 00:08:24,379
THE EXTERNAL JUGULAR.

184
00:08:24,421 --> 00:08:25,713
OH, UH...

185
00:08:25,755 --> 00:08:28,425
S-SUPERIOR...VENA CAVA.

186
00:08:28,467 --> 00:08:29,843
AND THAT LEADS TO?

187
00:08:29,884 --> 00:08:32,471
OH, EASY, THE SEAT
OF ALL JOY AND SADNESS.

188
00:08:32,512 --> 00:08:34,389
[ CHUCKLES ]

189
00:08:34,431 --> 00:08:36,724
PHYSIOLOGICALLY,
IT IS NOTHING MORE

190
00:08:36,766 --> 00:08:38,393
THAN A VERY EFFICIENT PUMP.

191
00:08:38,435 --> 00:08:41,062
WHAT COULD POSSIBLY
MAKE YOU PEOPLE THINK

192
00:08:41,104 --> 00:08:43,357
IT IS THE SOURCE
OF ALL EMOTION?

193
00:08:43,398 --> 00:08:46,318
YOU KNOW, YOU MAY KNOW ABOUT
OUR CARDIOPULMONARY SYSTEM,

194
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:49,570
BUT YOU HAVE A LOT TO LEARN
ABOUT THE HUMAN HEART.

195
00:08:49,612 --> 00:08:51,614
THIS IS ME.

196
00:08:51,656 --> 00:08:53,367
[ CHUCKLES ]

197
00:08:53,408 --> 00:08:54,534
PHLOX: GOOD NIGHT.

198
00:08:54,575 --> 00:08:56,995
OH, DOCTOR...

199
00:08:57,037 --> 00:08:58,746
I JUST WANTED TO THANK YOU.

200
00:08:58,788 --> 00:09:00,332
I-IT WAS FUN TONIGHT.

201
00:09:00,374 --> 00:09:02,000
YOU'RE WELCOME.

202
00:09:02,042 --> 00:09:04,711
UH, THEY'RE SHOWING
ANOTHER ONE NEXT WEEK.

203
00:09:04,752 --> 00:09:05,962
"SUNSET BOULEVARD."

204
00:09:06,004 --> 00:09:08,215
I THINK YOU MIGHT LIKE IT.

205
00:09:08,256 --> 00:09:10,384
I'M SURE I WILL.

206
00:09:10,425 --> 00:09:11,759
UM, SEE YOU TOMORROW?

207
00:09:11,801 --> 00:09:13,970
OH, SORRY [Chuckling] I FORGOT.

208
00:09:14,012 --> 00:09:15,763
DENOBULANS DON'T LIKE
TO BE TOUCHED.

209
00:09:15,805 --> 00:09:17,307
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

210
00:09:17,349 --> 00:09:20,560
I'M TRYING TO SHED SOME
OF MY CULTURAL INHIBITIONS.

211
00:09:20,601 --> 00:09:23,271
OH, IN THAT CASE...

212
00:09:23,313 --> 00:09:25,482
GOOD NIGHT.

213
00:09:32,697 --> 00:09:35,033
PHLOX:<i> SINCE WE WERE ON</i>
<i>THE SUBJECT OF MATING,</i>

214
00:09:35,075 --> 00:09:38,953
<i>I THINK CREWMAN CUTLER MAY BE</i>
<i>ROMANTICALLY INTERESTED IN ME.</i>

215
00:09:38,995 --> 00:09:40,621
<i>I CAN'T BE CERTAIN, HOWEVER.</i>

216
00:09:40,663 --> 00:09:42,749
<i>THE PHEROMONES OF HUMAN FEMALES</i>

217
00:09:42,790 --> 00:09:45,793
<i>AREN'T AS POTENT</i>
<i>AS DENOBULANS'.</i>

218
00:09:51,299 --> 00:09:55,220
ARE THERE ANY
INHABITED SYSTEMS NEARBY?

219
00:09:58,056 --> 00:09:59,682
THERE'S A
MINSHARA-CLASS PLANET

220
00:09:59,724 --> 00:10:01,309
LESS THAN A LIGHT-YEAR AWAY.

221
00:10:01,351 --> 00:10:04,354
THE SHIP'S NOT ANSWERING
OUR HAILS, CAPTAIN.

222
00:10:04,396 --> 00:10:07,648
REED: IT'S DEFINITELY PRE-WARP,
SIR. COULD BE UNMANNED.

223
00:10:07,690 --> 00:10:09,650
MAYBE A PROBE OF SOME KIND.

224
00:10:09,692 --> 00:10:12,028
ARCHER: ANY BIO-SIGNS?

225
00:10:18,493 --> 00:10:22,205
TWO, BUT THEY'RE VERY FAINT.

226
00:10:25,083 --> 00:10:27,252
BRING IT INTO LAUNCH BAY 2,

227
00:10:27,294 --> 00:10:32,549
AND TELL DR. PHLOX HE MIGHT HAVE
A COUPLE OF PATIENTS.

228
00:10:47,939 --> 00:10:51,025
WE...FOUND YOUR SHIP ADRIFT.

229
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:53,736
WE THOUGHT WE MIGHT
BE ABLE TO HELP.

230
00:10:53,778 --> 00:10:57,198
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE]

231
00:11:01,536 --> 00:11:04,456
I NEED A LITTLE MORE.

232
00:11:04,498 --> 00:11:05,999
I'M JONATHAN ARCHER.

233
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:08,335
YOU'RE ON THE
STARSHIP<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

234
00:11:08,376 --> 00:11:10,711
[ SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

235
00:11:16,551 --> 00:11:18,553
CAN YOU UNDERSTAND ME?

236
00:11:20,847 --> 00:11:22,599
WHO ARE YOU?

237
00:11:22,641 --> 00:11:24,518
WHAT PLANET?

238
00:11:24,559 --> 00:11:27,395
EARTH. WE ARE FROM EARTH.

239
00:11:27,437 --> 00:11:31,525
ALIEN: THIS...
IS A WARP VESSEL?

240
00:11:31,566 --> 00:11:33,776
YES.

241
00:11:36,070 --> 00:11:39,449
WE LEFT VALAKIS OVER A YEAR AGO,
ALONG WITH THREE OTHER SHIPS.

242
00:11:39,491 --> 00:11:40,783
WHY?

243
00:11:40,825 --> 00:11:44,787
YOU MUST HAVE NOTICED
OUR CONDITION BY NOW.

244
00:11:44,829 --> 00:11:46,998
PHLOX: I DETECTED THE ILLNESS.

245
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:49,959
12 MILLION OF US DIED
THE YEAR BEFORE WE LEFT.

246
00:11:50,001 --> 00:11:52,170
I CAN ONLY IMAGINE
HOW MANY HAVE DIED SINCE.

247
00:11:52,212 --> 00:11:55,549
OUR DOCTORS CAN'T FIND A CURE,

248
00:11:55,590 --> 00:11:56,715
BUT A MORE ADVANCED PEOPLE,

249
00:11:56,757 --> 00:12:00,970
PEOPLE WITH WARP TECHNOLOGY,
LIKE YOU,

250
00:12:01,012 --> 00:12:04,057
YOUR MEDICAL SCIENCE
MUST BE MORE EFFECTIVE.

251
00:12:04,098 --> 00:12:06,518
YOU'VE ENCOUNTERED OTHER
WARP-CAPABLE SPECIES?

252
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:09,229
THE M'KLEXA AND THE FERENGI.

253
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:11,523
THEY BOTH VISITED OUR WORLD.

254
00:12:11,565 --> 00:12:13,900
DO YOU KNOW THEM?

255
00:12:15,610 --> 00:12:17,904
NO.

256
00:12:20,114 --> 00:12:21,575
ARE YOU THE SHIP'S DOCTOR?

257
00:12:21,616 --> 00:12:24,411
PHLOX: I AM.

258
00:12:24,452 --> 00:12:26,037
MY PEOPLE ARE DYING.

259
00:12:26,079 --> 00:12:29,666
WILL YOU ALLOW HIM
TO HELP US?

260
00:12:35,754 --> 00:12:37,840
ANY THOUGHTS?

261
00:12:40,218 --> 00:12:42,053
THEY DID COME LOOKING FOR US,

262
00:12:42,095 --> 00:12:44,138
AND CONSIDERING
THEY'VE ALREADY MET

263
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:46,558
TWO OTHER
WARP-CAPABLE SPECIES...

264
00:12:48,976 --> 00:12:52,272
THE RISK OF
CONTAMINATION SEEMS...

265
00:12:52,313 --> 00:12:54,065
ACCEPTABLE.

266
00:12:56,568 --> 00:12:58,612
SEE WHAT YOU CAN DO.

267
00:12:58,653 --> 00:13:00,947
ALIEN: THANK YOU.

268
00:13:04,117 --> 00:13:06,745
PHLOX:<i> IF THIS LETTER ARRIVES</i>
<i>LATER THAN USUAL, DOCTOR,</i>

269
00:13:06,785 --> 00:13:08,329
<i>I HOPE YOU'LL FORGIVE ME.</i>

270
00:13:08,371 --> 00:13:10,957
<i>I'VE BEEN PRESENTED</i>
<i>WITH A RATHER UNUSUAL CASE</i>

271
00:13:10,998 --> 00:13:13,251
<i>INVOLVING A PAIR</i>
<i>OF ALIEN ASTRONAUTS.</i>

272
00:13:13,293 --> 00:13:16,504
<i>IT MAY NOT SURPRISE YOU</i>
<i>THAT THEY LANDED IN MY SICK BAY</i>

273
00:13:16,546 --> 00:13:19,591
<i>THROUGH AN ACT</i>
<i>OF HUMAN COMPASSION.</i>

274
00:13:25,597 --> 00:13:27,682
<i>I SAID BEFORE</i>
<i>THAT MY DUTIES ENTAIL</i>

275
00:13:27,724 --> 00:13:29,684
<i>THE OCCASIONAL EMERGENCY.</i>

276
00:13:29,726 --> 00:13:33,313
<i>EMERGENCIES, IT SEEMS,</i>
<i>COME IN ALL SHAPES AND SIZES.</i>

277
00:13:33,354 --> 00:13:35,982
<i>I WAS ONCE NEARLY OVERWHELMED</i>
<i>BY 50 PATIENTS</i>

278
00:13:36,023 --> 00:13:38,485
<i>IN A REFUGEE CAMP ON MATALAS.</i>

279
00:13:38,526 --> 00:13:41,946
<i>CAPTAIN ARCHER IS NOW ASKING ME</i>
<i>TO TAKE RESPONSIBILITY</i>

280
00:13:41,988 --> 00:13:44,949
<i>FOR OVER 50 MILLION.</i>

281
00:13:44,991 --> 00:13:47,410
[ HOSHI AND PHLOX
SPEAKING DENOBULAN ]

282
00:14:00,757 --> 00:14:02,425
HOSHI: UM...

283
00:14:04,385 --> 00:14:05,804
[ PHLOX CHUCKLES ]

284
00:14:13,394 --> 00:14:15,814
PHLOX, IN ENGLISH:
IT'S A NOSTRIL?

285
00:14:19,150 --> 00:14:21,361
[ CHUCKLES ]

286
00:14:21,402 --> 00:14:23,822
HOSHI, IN ENGLISH: I'VE NOTICED
YOU AND CREWMAN CUTLER

287
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:25,657
SPENDING A LOT OF TIME
TOGETHER.

288
00:14:25,699 --> 00:14:29,076
IS THERE SOMETHING
GOING ON BETWEEN YOU TWO?

289
00:14:29,118 --> 00:14:31,037
PHLOX: IN DENOBULAN, PLEASE.

290
00:14:31,078 --> 00:14:32,831
UM...

291
00:14:40,463 --> 00:14:43,591
PHLOX, SPEAKING ENGLISH:
I BELIEVE THE WORD YOU'RE
SEARCHING FOR IS "DATING."

292
00:14:43,633 --> 00:14:46,720
[ TRANSLATES "ARE YOU
TWO DATING?" IN DENOBULAN ]

293
00:14:46,761 --> 00:14:49,055
HOSHI, IN ENGLISH:
WELL, ARE YOU?

294
00:14:50,890 --> 00:14:52,600
[ SIGHS ]

295
00:15:01,275 --> 00:15:03,069
HOSHI, SPEAKING ENGLISH:
THERE ARE WAYS YOU CAN TELL.

296
00:15:16,499 --> 00:15:18,167
[IN ENGLISH]
TO MAKE PHYSICAL CONTACT?

297
00:15:18,209 --> 00:15:19,794
[IN ENGLISH] WELL, SHE DID
KISS ME ON THE CHEEK

298
00:15:19,836 --> 00:15:21,128
THE OTHER NIGHT.

299
00:15:21,170 --> 00:15:23,882
IN DENOBULAN, DOCTOR.

300
00:15:38,229 --> 00:15:40,106
[IN ENGLISH]
I BEG YOUR PARDON?

301
00:15:40,147 --> 00:15:41,566
HOSHI, IN ENGLISH:
COUPLE.

302
00:15:41,608 --> 00:15:44,277
[ Laughing ] CUTE COUPLE.

303
00:15:55,413 --> 00:15:57,081
REED: IT'S PRETTY CROWDED
OUT THERE.

304
00:15:57,123 --> 00:16:00,042
A LOT OF SPACECRAFT
AND ARTIFICIAL SATELLITES.

305
00:16:00,084 --> 00:16:02,128
TRAVIS: NOTHING
I CAN'T AVOID, SIR.

306
00:16:02,169 --> 00:16:05,757
ARCHER: PUT US IN A LOW ORBIT,
TRAVIS. THEY'RE EXPECTING US.

307
00:16:05,799 --> 00:16:08,426
PHLOX:<i> THE CAPTAIN HAS COMMITTED</i>
<i>ALL OUR RESOURCES</i>

308
00:16:08,468 --> 00:16:09,844
<i>TO HELPING PEOPLE</i>

309
00:16:09,886 --> 00:16:12,096
<i>HE DIDN'T EVEN KNOW EXISTED</i>
<i>TWO DAYS AGO.</i>

310
00:16:12,138 --> 00:16:14,808
<i>ONCE AGAIN, I AM STRUCK</i>
<i>BY YOUR SPECIES' DESIRE</i>

311
00:16:14,849 --> 00:16:16,559
<i>TO HELP OTHERS.</i>

312
00:16:21,522 --> 00:16:24,442
MAN: IT SEEMS THE MORE
AGGRESSIVELY
WE TREAT THE ILLNESS,

313
00:16:24,484 --> 00:16:25,777
THE MORE RESISTANT IT BECOMES.

314
00:16:25,819 --> 00:16:27,487
PHLOX: WHAT'S THE
CURRENT RATE OF INFECTION?

315
00:16:27,528 --> 00:16:28,780
MAN: ONE OUT OF THREE.

316
00:16:28,822 --> 00:16:30,657
ARCHER: IT'S A
FULL-BLOWN EPIDEMIC.

317
00:16:30,698 --> 00:16:33,159
MAN: THESE ARE IN THE MOST
ADVANCED STAGE.

318
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:34,702
PHLOX: HMM.

319
00:16:34,744 --> 00:16:37,455
YOU'RE TREATING THEM
WITH A SYNTHETIC ANTIBODY?

320
00:16:37,497 --> 00:16:40,667
MAN: IT'S EFFECTIVE AT FIRST,
BUT THE DISEASE MUTATES.

321
00:16:40,708 --> 00:16:42,585
ONCE IT MOVES INTO
THE RESPIRATORY SYSTEM,

322
00:16:42,627 --> 00:16:44,128
THERE'S NO WAY
OF CONTROLLING IT.

323
00:16:44,170 --> 00:16:46,965
PULMONARY FAILURE
USUALLY FOLLOWS IN A FEW DAYS.

324
00:16:47,006 --> 00:16:49,133
PHLOX: CAPTAIN,
TREATMENT WITH PRIAXATE

325
00:16:49,175 --> 00:16:50,677
SHOULD EASE THE SYMPTOMS
IN THE SICKEST PATIENTS,

326
00:16:50,718 --> 00:16:52,887
AT LEAST TEMPORARILY.

327
00:16:52,929 --> 00:16:54,472
I CAN EASILY SHOW THE VALAKIANS

328
00:16:54,514 --> 00:16:56,516
HOW TO SYNTHESIZE
AS MUCH AS THEY NEED.

329
00:16:56,557 --> 00:16:57,892
ARCHER: GO AHEAD.

330
00:16:57,934 --> 00:16:59,853
PHLOX: I'LL NEED ALL
THE LAB WORK YOU HAVE

331
00:16:59,894 --> 00:17:02,981
AND CASE HISTORIES OF PATIENTS
IN EVERY STAGE OF THE DISEASE.

332
00:17:03,063 --> 00:17:04,482
MAN: CERTAINLY.

333
00:17:15,117 --> 00:17:16,577
HOSHI: EXCUSE ME.

334
00:17:16,619 --> 00:17:18,621
WE'RE THE ONES
THAT BROUGHT HIM HERE.

335
00:17:18,663 --> 00:17:20,206
CAN YOU TELL ME
HOW HE'S DOING?

336
00:17:20,247 --> 00:17:22,876
[ MAN SPEAKING MENK ]

337
00:17:22,917 --> 00:17:26,880
I'M SORRY.
COULD YOU SAY THAT AGAIN?

338
00:17:28,548 --> 00:17:31,843
WE SHOULD ASSIGN
SOME CREWMEN TO WATCH

339
00:17:31,885 --> 00:17:33,636
DR. PHLOX AND HIS EQUIPMENT.

340
00:17:33,678 --> 00:17:37,056
I DON'T THINK THESE PEOPLE
ARE ABOUT TO STEAL ANYTHING.

341
00:17:37,097 --> 00:17:39,559
YOUR EXPERIENCE
WITH LESSER CIVILIZATIONS

342
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:41,352
IS LIMITED, CAPTAIN.

343
00:17:41,394 --> 00:17:44,230
YOU MIGHT BE SURPRISED
WHAT A TEMPTATION

344
00:17:44,271 --> 00:17:45,982
OUR TECHNOLOGY CAN BE.

345
00:17:46,024 --> 00:17:48,150
[ MAN CONTINUES IN MENK ]

346
00:17:54,198 --> 00:17:55,575
ARCHER: HOSHI?

347
00:17:55,616 --> 00:17:58,244
CAPTAIN, THE U.T. CAN'T
TRANSLATE HIS LANGUAGE.

348
00:17:58,285 --> 00:18:00,872
[ MAN SPEAKING MENK ]

349
00:18:00,914 --> 00:18:03,374
HOSHI: HE DOESN'T SPEAK
THE SAME LANGUAGE AS YOU?

350
00:18:03,416 --> 00:18:05,376
NO. HE'S MENK.

351
00:18:05,418 --> 00:18:08,046
THEY'RE NOT AS EVOLVED
AS VALAKIANS,

352
00:18:08,087 --> 00:18:09,714
BUT THEY'RE VERY HARD WORKERS.

353
00:18:09,756 --> 00:18:11,966
ARCHER: THEY'RE INDIGENOUS
TO THIS PLANET?

354
00:18:12,008 --> 00:18:13,676
MAN: IS THAT SO STRANGE?

355
00:18:13,718 --> 00:18:16,470
ON MOST OF THE PLANETS
WE'VE ENCOUNTERED,

356
00:18:16,512 --> 00:18:19,265
ONLY ONE SPECIES
OF HUMANOIDS SURVIVED

357
00:18:19,306 --> 00:18:20,808
THE EVOLUTIONARY PROCESS.

358
00:18:20,850 --> 00:18:24,186
YOU TWO ARE NOT
FROM THE SAME PLANET?

359
00:18:24,228 --> 00:18:27,023
NO.

360
00:18:27,065 --> 00:18:31,360
WE MAY LOOK ALIKE,
BUT THE SIMILARITY ENDS THERE.

361
00:18:31,402 --> 00:18:33,279
PHLOX: I DON'T SEE ANY MENK
PATIENTS HERE.

362
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:34,447
WHERE ARE THEY BEING TREATED?

363
00:18:34,488 --> 00:18:35,990
THEY HAVEN'T CONTRACTED
THE DISEASE.

364
00:18:36,032 --> 00:18:39,326
PHLOX: HAVE YOU LOOKED
INTO THEIR IMMUNITY?

365
00:18:39,368 --> 00:18:40,954
MAN: IT WAS ONE OF THE
FIRST THINGS WE PURSUED,

366
00:18:40,995 --> 00:18:44,624
BUT MENK AND VALAKIAN ARE
PHYSIOLOGICALLY INCOMPATIBLE.

367
00:18:44,665 --> 00:18:46,208
PHLOX: STILL, IT
COULD BE SIGNIFICANT.

368
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:48,586
I'D LIKE TO SEE YOUR
DATA ON THE MENK, AS WELL.

369
00:18:48,628 --> 00:18:50,546
MAN: OF COURSE.

370
00:18:50,588 --> 00:18:53,967
PHLOX:<i> I HAD MEANT TO TRANSMIT</i>
<i>THIS LETTER BY NOW,</i>

371
00:18:54,008 --> 00:18:55,509
<i>BUT THE VALAKIAN EPIDEMIC</i>

372
00:18:55,551 --> 00:18:58,178
<i>HAS BEEN TAKING UP</i>
<i>MOST OF MY TIME.</i>

373
00:18:58,220 --> 00:19:01,140
<i>WORKING WITH THE PHYSICIANS</i>
<i>HERE HAS BEEN QUITE FULFILLING.</i>

374
00:19:01,181 --> 00:19:03,517
<i>I SUPPOSE IT'S THE REASON</i>
<i>WE JOINED</i>

375
00:19:03,559 --> 00:19:05,770
<i>THE INTERSPECIES</i>
<i>MEDICAL EXCHANGE.</i>

376
00:19:05,812 --> 00:19:09,107
<i>BUT I WORRY ABOUT FALSELY</i>
<i>RAISING THEIR HOPES.</i>

377
00:19:09,148 --> 00:19:11,442
<i>DESPITE CAPTAIN ARCHER'S</i>
<i>CONFIDENCE IN ME,</i>

378
00:19:11,484 --> 00:19:13,778
<i>I'M AFRAID THE SCALE</i>
<i>OF THE DISASTER</i>

379
00:19:13,820 --> 00:19:17,115
<i>MAY OUTWEIGH</i>
<i>OUR BEST INTENTIONS.</i>

380
00:19:17,156 --> 00:19:21,285
<i>I'VE DECIDED TO ENLIST CREWMAN</i>
<i>CUTLER'S HELP IN MY TASK.</i>

381
00:19:21,327 --> 00:19:23,746
CUTLER: SO WHAT ARE
THE MENK LIKE?

382
00:19:23,788 --> 00:19:25,915
YOU'LL HAVE THE CHANCE
TO SEE FOR YOURSELF.

383
00:19:25,957 --> 00:19:26,958
CUTLER: AH!

384
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:29,585
YOU'RE A TRAINED EXOBIOLOGIST.

385
00:19:29,627 --> 00:19:32,254
I'D FIND YOUR ASSISTANCE
IN THE FIELD INVALUABLE.

386
00:19:32,296 --> 00:19:33,297
THANK YOU, DOCTOR.

387
00:19:33,339 --> 00:19:34,799
PHLOX:<i> ON A PERSONAL NOTE,</i>

388
00:19:34,841 --> 00:19:37,010
<i>THE AFFECTION CREWMAN CUTLER</i>
<i>IS SHOWING</i>

389
00:19:37,051 --> 00:19:39,137
<i>HAS LEFT ME A BIT PERPLEXED,</i>

390
00:19:39,178 --> 00:19:41,388
<i>SO I'VE DECIDED TO DISCUSS IT</i>
<i>WITH THE ONE PERSON ON BOARD</i>

391
00:19:41,430 --> 00:19:44,934
<i>WHO MIGHT UNDERSTAND THE</i>
<i>COMPLEXITIES OF THE SITUATION.</i>

392
00:19:44,976 --> 00:19:46,644
THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

393
00:19:46,686 --> 00:19:48,062
PHLOX: IT'S NOTHING
TO BE ASHAMED OF.

394
00:19:48,104 --> 00:19:49,689
MY TEETH WERE SEALED

395
00:19:49,730 --> 00:19:52,608
WITH A TRI-FLUORINATE
COMPOUND 23 YEARS AGO.

396
00:19:52,650 --> 00:19:54,152
WELL, NORMAL WEAR AND TEAR

397
00:19:54,193 --> 00:19:56,362
HAS ALLOWED SOME
DECAY TO SNEAK IN.

398
00:19:56,403 --> 00:19:58,447
SEE FOR YOURSELF, HMM?

399
00:19:58,489 --> 00:20:02,284
THERE, ON YOUR
ANTERIOR TRICUSPID.

400
00:20:06,039 --> 00:20:07,665
I'M SURE YOU HAVE
MORE PRESSING CONCERNS.

401
00:20:07,707 --> 00:20:09,416
I'LL COME BACK LATER.

402
00:20:09,458 --> 00:20:12,336
I'M WAITING FOR THE COMPUTER
TO ANALYZE SOME TISSUE SAMPLES.

403
00:20:12,378 --> 00:20:15,422
IT'LL ONLY TAKE A MOMENT
TO REPAIR.

404
00:20:24,140 --> 00:20:26,600
OPEN, PLEASE.

405
00:20:26,642 --> 00:20:28,477
WIDER.

406
00:20:32,940 --> 00:20:34,650
UM...YOU'VE LIVED AMONG HUMANS

407
00:20:34,692 --> 00:20:37,195
FOR QUITE SOME TIME
NOW, SUBCOMMANDER.

408
00:20:37,236 --> 00:20:39,697
I'M--I'M CURIOUS --
HAVE YOU EVER KNOWN THEM

409
00:20:39,739 --> 00:20:41,615
TO MATE OUTSIDE THEIR SPECIES?

410
00:20:41,657 --> 00:20:43,283
[ MUMBLING ]

411
00:20:43,325 --> 00:20:44,451
AH! THERE IT IS.

412
00:20:44,493 --> 00:20:47,788
[ CHUCKLES, CLEARS THROAT ]

413
00:20:49,498 --> 00:20:51,375
ARE YOU ASKING

414
00:20:51,417 --> 00:20:54,128
OUT OF PERSONAL INTEREST
OR SCIENTIFIC CURIOSITY?

415
00:20:54,170 --> 00:20:56,089
BOTH, I SUPPOSE.

416
00:20:56,130 --> 00:20:58,883
THERE'S A CREWMAN ON BOARD
I'VE BECOME CLOSE WITH.

417
00:20:58,925 --> 00:21:01,969
I THINK SHE'S ATTRACTED TO ME.

418
00:21:02,011 --> 00:21:03,387
T'POL: IN MY EXPERIENCE,

419
00:21:03,429 --> 00:21:06,140
HUMANS LACK THE...
EMOTIONAL MATURITY

420
00:21:06,182 --> 00:21:07,975
FOR INTERSPECIES RELATIONSHIPS.

421
00:21:08,017 --> 00:21:10,436
THEY TEND TO BE
EASILY INFATUATED

422
00:21:10,477 --> 00:21:12,105
WITH THINGS THEY FIND NEW.

423
00:21:12,146 --> 00:21:16,150
THIS CREWMAN MAY SIMPLY BE
SATISFYING HER CURIOSITY

424
00:21:16,192 --> 00:21:18,027
AT YOUR EXPENSE.

425
00:21:21,488 --> 00:21:23,407
OPEN.

426
00:21:23,449 --> 00:21:26,744
PHLOX: <i> SUBCOMMANDER T'POL HAS</i>
<i>A VERY PRAGMATIC VIEW</i>

427
00:21:26,786 --> 00:21:27,954
<i>OF THE UNIVERSE.</i>

428
00:21:27,995 --> 00:21:29,288
<i>I ADMIRE HER LOGIC,</i>

429
00:21:29,329 --> 00:21:31,331
<i>ALTHOUGH SHE LACKS</i>
<i>THE INSTINCTIVENESS</i>

430
00:21:31,373 --> 00:21:34,668
<i>THAT A MORE EMOTIONAL RESPONSE</i>
<i>CAN PROVIDE.</i>

431
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:37,671
<i>SOMEHOW,</i>
<i>I FIND THIS UNSETTLING.</i>

432
00:21:37,713 --> 00:21:41,008
THERE. THAT WASN'T SO BAD.

433
00:21:43,094 --> 00:21:46,305
THANKS FOR YOUR INSIGHTS.

434
00:21:46,346 --> 00:21:48,057
BE CAREFUL.

435
00:21:54,772 --> 00:21:56,356
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

436
00:21:56,398 --> 00:21:57,900
COME IN.

437
00:22:00,236 --> 00:22:02,321
YOU ASKED TO SEE ME, CAPTAIN?

438
00:22:02,362 --> 00:22:03,447
I JUST GOT A CALL

439
00:22:03,489 --> 00:22:05,407
FROM THE DIRECTOR
OF THE CLINIC.

440
00:22:05,449 --> 00:22:08,744
HE'S EAGER TO HEAR
IF YOU'VE MADE ANY PROGRESS.

441
00:22:12,081 --> 00:22:13,916
DOCTOR?

442
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:17,544
I'VE DEVELOPED A MEDICATION

443
00:22:17,586 --> 00:22:24,260
TO EASE THE SYMPTOMS
OF THE DISEASE, BUT...

444
00:22:24,302 --> 00:22:26,304
BUT?

445
00:22:28,806 --> 00:22:33,936
THIS EPIDEMIC ISN'T BEING CAUSED
BY A VIRUS OR BACTERIA.

446
00:22:33,978 --> 00:22:37,815
THE PROTEINS THAT BIND THEIR
CHROMOSOMES ARE DETERIORATING.

447
00:22:37,857 --> 00:22:39,108
THEIR ILLNESS IS GENETIC.

448
00:22:39,150 --> 00:22:41,610
IT'S BEEN GOING ON
FOR THOUSANDS OF YEARS,

449
00:22:41,652 --> 00:22:44,071
BUT THE RATE OF MUTATION
HAS ACCELERATED

450
00:22:44,113 --> 00:22:46,490
OVER THE LAST FEW GENERATIONS.

451
00:22:46,532 --> 00:22:51,120
BASED ON MY PROJECTIONS,
THE VALAKIANS WILL BE EXTINCT

452
00:22:51,162 --> 00:22:53,497
IN LESS THAN TWO CENTURIES.

453
00:22:54,832 --> 00:22:57,335
I WISH I HAD BETTER NEWS.

454
00:23:01,714 --> 00:23:03,090
WHAT ABOUT A CURE?

455
00:23:03,132 --> 00:23:05,926
GENETIC ABNORMALITIES
ON THIS LEVEL

456
00:23:05,968 --> 00:23:08,386
ARE VERY DIFFICULT TO REVERSE.

457
00:23:08,428 --> 00:23:10,639
BUT NOT IMPOSSIBLE.

458
00:23:10,681 --> 00:23:13,684
NO. I STILL BELIEVE
THE MENK IMMUNITY

459
00:23:13,726 --> 00:23:15,895
COULD BE THE KEY TO A CURE.

460
00:23:15,936 --> 00:23:18,022
I PLAN TO STUDY THEM
IN MORE DETAIL.

461
00:23:18,064 --> 00:23:20,233
TAKE ALL THE TIME YOU NEED.

462
00:23:37,499 --> 00:23:39,417
PHLOX:<i> WHEN I BEGAN</i>
<i>TO PRACTICE MEDICINE,</i>

463
00:23:39,459 --> 00:23:43,256
<i>I HAD NO IDEA IT WOULD TAKE ME</i>
<i>ON JOURNEYS TO OTHER WORLDS.</i>

464
00:23:43,297 --> 00:23:45,007
<i>EVERY SPECIES I ENCOUNTER</i>

465
00:23:45,049 --> 00:23:47,968
<i>ALLOWS ME TO EXPLORE</i>
<i>A NEW PHYSIOLOGY.</i>

466
00:23:48,010 --> 00:23:50,346
<i>AT THE MOMENT, I FIND MYSELF</i>
<i>IN THE ENVIABLE POSITION</i>

467
00:23:50,388 --> 00:23:53,057
<i>OF STUDYING TWO HUMANOIDS</i>
<i>FROM THE SAME PLANET.</i>

468
00:23:53,099 --> 00:23:57,186
<i>IT'S A RARE</i>
<i>AND EXCITING OPPORTUNITY.</i>

469
00:23:58,687 --> 00:24:01,023
PHLOX: TELL THEM WE'D LIKE
TO RUN SOME TESTS,

470
00:24:01,065 --> 00:24:02,691
TAKE SAMPLES OF THEIR BLOOD.

471
00:24:02,733 --> 00:24:04,610
IT WILL BE COMPLETELY PAINLESS.

472
00:24:04,651 --> 00:24:07,947
[ HOSHI SPEAKING
ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

473
00:24:07,988 --> 00:24:10,032
[ MAN SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

474
00:24:15,288 --> 00:24:17,790
HE SAYS
THEY'D BE HAPPY TO HELP.

475
00:24:17,831 --> 00:24:20,293
PHLOX:<i> AS FASCINATING</i>
<i>AS THE TWO SPECIES ARE</i>

476
00:24:20,334 --> 00:24:22,211
<i>FROM A BIOLOGICAL STANDPOINT,</i>

477
00:24:22,253 --> 00:24:26,299
<i>IT'S THEIR ABILITY TO COEXIST</i>
<i>THAT INTRIGUES ME THE MOST.</i>

478
00:24:26,340 --> 00:24:27,925
<i>THE VALAKIANS</i>
<i>ARE HIGHLY EVOLVED,</i>

479
00:24:27,967 --> 00:24:29,551
<i>TECHNOLOGICALLY ADVANCED,</i>

480
00:24:29,593 --> 00:24:33,764
<i>WHILE THE MENK ARE RELATIVELY</i>
<i>PRIMITIVE BY COMPARISON.</i>

481
00:24:33,806 --> 00:24:35,515
<i>TO MY SURPRISE, THE TWO SEEM</i>

482
00:24:35,557 --> 00:24:38,852
<i>TO BE LIVING SIDE-BY-SIDE,</i>
<i>PEACEFULLY.</i>

483
00:24:40,646 --> 00:24:42,022
[ HOSHI SPEAKING
ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

484
00:24:42,064 --> 00:24:46,444
[ MAN SPEAKING ALIEN
LANGUAGE]

485
00:24:53,909 --> 00:24:57,246
[ DEVICE PULSATING ]

486
00:24:59,665 --> 00:25:01,208
[ MAN SPEAKING
ALIEN LANGUAGE ]

487
00:25:03,336 --> 00:25:05,212
HE WANTS TO KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

488
00:25:05,254 --> 00:25:07,006
HAVE YOU LEARNED ENOUGH MENK

489
00:25:07,047 --> 00:25:09,633
TO EXPLAIN
A MOLECULAR BIOSCAN?

490
00:25:09,675 --> 00:25:12,970
DOCTOR...UM...

491
00:25:13,012 --> 00:25:15,097
[ HOSHI SPEAKING MENK ]

492
00:25:20,394 --> 00:25:21,895
CUTLER: WHAT'D YOU SAY?

493
00:25:21,937 --> 00:25:25,232
I TOLD HIM THE DOCTOR
WAS LOOKING INSIDE OF HIM.

494
00:25:28,735 --> 00:25:30,696
THANK YOU.

495
00:25:30,737 --> 00:25:32,656
[ HOSHI SPEAKING MENK ]

496
00:25:32,698 --> 00:25:34,908
[ MAN SPEAKING MENK ]

497
00:25:34,950 --> 00:25:37,828
YOU'RE WELCOME.

498
00:25:37,870 --> 00:25:40,706
[ MAN SPEAKING MENK ]

499
00:25:40,747 --> 00:25:42,666
FOOD.

500
00:25:42,708 --> 00:25:44,668
CUTLER: DID HE
JUST SAY "FOOD"?

501
00:25:44,710 --> 00:25:46,003
[ MAN SPEAKING MENK ]
FOOD.

502
00:25:46,045 --> 00:25:47,671
PHLOX: HAVE YOU BEEN
TEACHING HIM ENGLISH?

503
00:25:47,713 --> 00:25:50,674
HOSHI: NO, HE MUST HAVE PICKED
IT UP BY LISTENING TO US.

504
00:25:50,716 --> 00:25:53,511
PHLOX: HMM, PERHAPS WE FOUND
AN ASSISTANT COM OFFICER.

505
00:25:56,472 --> 00:25:57,723
NO FOOD.

506
00:25:57,764 --> 00:25:59,725
[ HOSHI SPEAKING MENK ]

507
00:25:59,766 --> 00:26:01,352
[ MAN SPEAKING MENK ]

508
00:26:04,688 --> 00:26:07,316
PHLOX: HMM, I HAVEN'T SEEN
ANY CROPS OR LIVESTOCK.

509
00:26:07,358 --> 00:26:10,361
I WONDER WHERE THEY GET THIS.

510
00:26:10,403 --> 00:26:13,739
[ HOSHI SPEAKING MENK ]

511
00:26:13,780 --> 00:26:17,410
[ MAN SPEAKING MENK ]

512
00:26:17,451 --> 00:26:20,204
HE SAYS THE SOIL HERE
ISN'T GOOD FOR PLANTING.

513
00:26:20,246 --> 00:26:22,164
[ MAN SPEAKING MENK ]

514
00:26:26,001 --> 00:26:27,669
HOSHI: THE VALAKIANS

515
00:26:27,711 --> 00:26:30,714
DON'T LET THEM LIVE
WHERE THE LAND IS FERTILE.

516
00:26:30,756 --> 00:26:32,925
[ MAN SPEAKING MENK ]

517
00:26:34,968 --> 00:26:38,180
THE VALAKIANS GIVE THEM
WHATEVER THEY NEED --

518
00:26:38,222 --> 00:26:40,099
FOOD, CLOTHING, MEDICINE.

519
00:26:40,140 --> 00:26:43,227
[ MAN SPEAKING MENK ]

520
00:26:43,269 --> 00:26:47,189
HOSHI: HE SAYS THE VALAKIANS
ARE GOOD TO THEM.

521
00:26:47,231 --> 00:26:49,567
THEY PROTECT THEM.

522
00:26:52,986 --> 00:26:54,696
PHLOX: MMM.

523
00:26:58,534 --> 00:27:01,661
PHLOX:<i> DESPITE THE MENK'S</i>
<i>INSISTENCE THAT THEY'RE</i>
<i>TREATED WELL,</i>

524
00:27:01,703 --> 00:27:05,832
<i>MY HUMAN CREWMATES</i>
<i>SEEM TO SEE THINGS DIFFERENTLY.</i>

525
00:27:05,874 --> 00:27:08,752
[ CUTLER SPEAKING MENK ]

526
00:27:08,794 --> 00:27:11,380
WELL, THAT'S THE LAST ONE.

527
00:27:11,422 --> 00:27:15,175
PHLOX:<i> THEY THINK THE MENK</i>
<i>ARE BEING EXPLOITED</i>
<i>BY THE VALAKIANS,</i>

528
00:27:15,217 --> 00:27:18,220
<i>SO THEIR FIRST INSTINCT</i>
<i>IS TO RISE TO THEIR DEFENSE,</i>

529
00:27:18,262 --> 00:27:19,930
<i>DESPITE THE FACT</i>

530
00:27:19,972 --> 00:27:23,976
<i>THAT THE MENK DON'T APPEAR</i>
<i>TO NEED OR WANT A DEFENDER.</i>

531
00:27:24,017 --> 00:27:26,061
PHLOX: WAIT A MOMENT.

532
00:27:31,150 --> 00:27:32,359
IMPRESSIVE.

533
00:27:32,401 --> 00:27:33,819
WHAT'D HE DO?

534
00:27:33,860 --> 00:27:36,489
HE'S GROUPED THE SAMPLES
TOGETHER BY FAMILY.

535
00:27:36,530 --> 00:27:40,534
CROSS-REFERENCED
BY BLOODLINES AND MARRIAGE

536
00:27:40,576 --> 00:27:44,538
IF I'M INTERPRETING
THE COLOR CODES CORRECTLY.

537
00:27:44,580 --> 00:27:46,499
[ PHLOX SPEAKING MENK ]

538
00:27:46,540 --> 00:27:48,167
PHLOX:<i> ON THE SURFACE,</i>

539
00:27:48,208 --> 00:27:50,210
<i>THE MENK APPEAR</i>
<i>TO BE A PRIMITIVE SPECIES,</i>

540
00:27:50,252 --> 00:27:52,296
<i>UNSOPHISTICATED</i>
<i>EVEN BY HUMAN STANDARDS --</i>

541
00:27:52,338 --> 00:27:53,922
<i>NO OFFENSE.</i>

542
00:27:53,964 --> 00:27:57,510
<i>BUT THEIR ABILITIES APPEAR</i>
<i>TO HAVE BEEN UNDERESTIMATED,</i>

543
00:27:57,551 --> 00:28:01,180
<i>EVEN BY MYSELF.</i>

544
00:28:01,221 --> 00:28:03,390
CUTLER: IT SEEMS
LIKE A VACATION,

545
00:28:03,432 --> 00:28:07,478
IF I DIDN'T KEEP REMEMBERING
WHY WE WERE HERE.

546
00:28:07,520 --> 00:28:10,481
HOSHI: I'M GOING TO HELP LARR
FINISH PACKING UP.

547
00:28:10,523 --> 00:28:13,942
HE'S BACK ON DUTY
AT THE HOSPITAL IN AN HOUR.

548
00:28:18,989 --> 00:28:21,492
THIS REALLY DOESN'T BOTHER YOU.

549
00:28:21,534 --> 00:28:22,993
WHAT?

550
00:28:23,035 --> 00:28:25,245
THE WAY THE VALAKIANS
TREAT THEM.

551
00:28:25,287 --> 00:28:26,539
WHY SHOULD IT?

552
00:28:26,580 --> 00:28:28,790
ON MOST WORLDS WITH
TWO HUMANOID SPECIES,

553
00:28:28,832 --> 00:28:31,502
ONE WOULD HAVE DRIVEN
THE OTHER TO EXTINCTION.

554
00:28:31,544 --> 00:28:33,962
HERE, THEY'VE DEVELOPED
A SYMBIOTIC RELATIONSHIP

555
00:28:34,004 --> 00:28:36,215
THAT SEEMS TO WORK QUITE WELL.

556
00:28:36,256 --> 00:28:38,258
THEY FORCE THE MENK
TO LIVE IN COMPOUNDS.

557
00:28:38,300 --> 00:28:40,594
THEY TREAT THEM
ALMOST LIKE PETS.

558
00:28:40,636 --> 00:28:44,181
THEIR CULTURE IS DIFFERENT.
IT'S...THEIR WAY.

559
00:28:44,223 --> 00:28:47,184
DOESN'T MAKE IT RIGHT.

560
00:28:47,226 --> 00:28:49,936
ARE YOU MARRIED, CREWMAN?

561
00:28:49,978 --> 00:28:51,980
[ Chuckling ] OF COURSE NOT.

562
00:28:52,022 --> 00:28:53,857
I WOULD HAVE TOLD YOU.

563
00:28:53,899 --> 00:28:55,484
I'M MARRIED.

564
00:28:55,526 --> 00:28:56,902
YOU ARE?

565
00:28:56,943 --> 00:28:59,071
THREE TIMES.

566
00:28:59,112 --> 00:29:01,865
SO YOU HAVE TWO EX-WIVES?

567
00:29:01,907 --> 00:29:03,367
I HAVE THREE CURRENT WIVES,

568
00:29:03,409 --> 00:29:05,411
AND THEY EACH HAVE
TWO HUSBANDS --

569
00:29:05,452 --> 00:29:07,246
NOT COUNTING MYSELF.

570
00:29:07,287 --> 00:29:11,917
IS THAT CONSIDERED NORMAL
FOR DENOBULANS?

571
00:29:11,958 --> 00:29:13,960
QUITE.

572
00:29:16,922 --> 00:29:18,798
WHY ARE YOU
TELLING ME THIS?

573
00:29:18,840 --> 00:29:20,926
I'VE BEEN GETTING
CERTAIN SIGNALS FROM YOU

574
00:29:20,967 --> 00:29:22,969
THAT SUGGEST
YOU MAY BE INTERESTED

575
00:29:23,011 --> 00:29:25,431
IN A ROMANTIC RELATIONSHIP
WITH ME.

576
00:29:27,641 --> 00:29:28,767
OH.

577
00:29:28,808 --> 00:29:32,896
UNLESS I MISINTERPRETED
THOSE SIGNALS.

578
00:29:32,938 --> 00:29:35,524
YOU DIDN'T.

579
00:29:35,566 --> 00:29:39,778
BUT I STILL DON'T KNOW
WHY YOU'RE TELLING ME THIS.

580
00:29:39,819 --> 00:29:44,366
YOU NEED TO KNOW
THAT MY CULTURE IS DIFFERENT.

581
00:29:44,408 --> 00:29:45,618
THAT DOESN'T MATTER.

582
00:29:45,659 --> 00:29:46,910
IT DOESN'T?

583
00:29:46,952 --> 00:29:48,245
THIS CULTURE'S DIFFERENT.

584
00:29:48,287 --> 00:29:50,205
THAT SEEMS TO MATTER TO YOU
A GREAT DEAL.

585
00:29:50,247 --> 00:29:53,584
PHLOX...

586
00:29:53,626 --> 00:29:57,879
AS FAR AS YOUR...
EXTENDED FAMILY GOES,

587
00:29:57,921 --> 00:30:02,175
I'M NOT INTERESTED IN
BECOMING WIFE NUMBER FOUR.

588
00:30:02,217 --> 00:30:04,052
[ CHUCKLES ]

589
00:30:04,094 --> 00:30:06,639
I JUST WANT TO BE YOUR FRIEND.

590
00:30:09,099 --> 00:30:11,435
WHAT DO YOU MEAN BY "FRIEND"?

591
00:30:11,477 --> 00:30:15,731
LET'S JUST SEE WHERE IT GOES.

592
00:30:40,005 --> 00:30:44,176
CAPTAIN...
I'M GLAD YOU COULD COME.

593
00:30:44,217 --> 00:30:47,638
IT WAS NO PROBLEM.

594
00:30:49,055 --> 00:30:51,767
HOW ARE YOU FEELING?

595
00:30:51,809 --> 00:30:55,061
THE MEDICATION YOU GAVE US
HELPS WITH THE PAIN.

596
00:30:55,103 --> 00:30:58,398
BUT MY...

597
00:30:58,440 --> 00:31:02,402
PROGNOSIS HASN'T CHANGED.

598
00:31:02,444 --> 00:31:05,197
WE'RE TRYING TO DO
SOMETHING ABOUT THAT.

599
00:31:05,238 --> 00:31:08,450
I HAVE A LOT OF FAITH
IN DR. PHLOX.

600
00:31:11,787 --> 00:31:13,079
I WANTED TO THANK YOU

601
00:31:13,121 --> 00:31:15,791
FOR GETTING ME HOME
BEFORE IT WAS TOO LATE.

602
00:31:15,833 --> 00:31:18,960
IT TOOK US A YEAR
TO GET OUT TO WHERE

603
00:31:19,002 --> 00:31:21,421
YOU FOUND US --
YOU BROUGHT US HOME IN A DAY.

604
00:31:21,463 --> 00:31:25,718
WE STARTED OUT IN SHIPS
VERY SIMILAR TO YOURS.

605
00:31:25,759 --> 00:31:30,430
SOMEDAY YOU'LL BE TRAVELING
JUST AS FAST AS WE ARE.

606
00:31:30,472 --> 00:31:33,726
SOMEDAY MAY NOT BE SOON ENOUGH.

607
00:31:33,767 --> 00:31:37,813
IF YOUR DOCTOR CAN'T HELP US...

608
00:31:37,855 --> 00:31:41,483
WE'LL NEED TO KEEP SEARCHING
FOR OTHERS THAT CAN.

609
00:31:43,109 --> 00:31:46,071
WE NEED WARP DRIVE.

610
00:31:46,112 --> 00:31:48,323
A MILLION MORE OF US WILL DIE

611
00:31:48,365 --> 00:31:51,785
BEFORE OUR NEXT SHIP
EVEN LEAVES THIS SYSTEM.

612
00:31:51,827 --> 00:31:53,245
WITH WARP ENGINES,

613
00:31:53,286 --> 00:31:55,539
WE WON'T HAVE TO WAIT
FOR PEOPLE TO FIND US.

614
00:31:55,581 --> 00:31:57,624
WE CAN SEEK HELP ON OUR OWN.

615
00:31:57,666 --> 00:32:01,253
YOU MAY NOT FIND
THAT EVERYONE YOU MEET

616
00:32:01,294 --> 00:32:03,088
WANTS TO HELP YOU.

617
00:32:03,129 --> 00:32:08,009
STILL, WE HAVE TO TRY.

618
00:32:09,219 --> 00:32:12,180
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]

619
00:32:14,140 --> 00:32:15,434
ARCHER.

620
00:32:15,475 --> 00:32:17,394
PHLOX: It's Phlox, Captain.

621
00:32:17,436 --> 00:32:19,979
We've collected all the samples.

622
00:32:20,021 --> 00:32:23,901
I'LL MEET YOU AT THE SHUTTLEPOD.
ARCHER OUT.

623
00:32:50,176 --> 00:32:52,387
ANYTHING TO REPORT?

624
00:32:52,429 --> 00:32:54,848
WE'VE RECEIVED 29 HAILS
IN THE PAST TWO HOURS.

625
00:32:54,890 --> 00:32:56,850
FROM WHOM?

626
00:32:56,892 --> 00:32:59,436
APPARENTLY, WORD OF OUR ARRIVAL
HAS SPREAD QUICKLY.

627
00:32:59,478 --> 00:33:01,814
OTHER CLINICS
ARE REQUESTING HELP.

628
00:33:01,855 --> 00:33:04,441
TWO ORBITAL SPACECRAFT
APPROACHED US

629
00:33:04,483 --> 00:33:06,109
WHILE YOU WERE ON THE PLANET.

630
00:33:06,151 --> 00:33:10,155
THEY MISTAKENLY BELIEVED
THAT WE ALREADY HAD A CURE.

631
00:33:10,196 --> 00:33:13,659
WE HAD TO TURN THEM AWAY.

632
00:33:17,203 --> 00:33:18,997
DO YOU HAVE A MINUTE?

633
00:33:36,222 --> 00:33:40,310
THE VALAKIANS WANT
OUR WARP TECHNOLOGY.

634
00:33:40,352 --> 00:33:42,855
WHAT DID YOU TELL THEM?

635
00:33:42,896 --> 00:33:47,192
THAT I'D THINK ABOUT IT.

636
00:33:47,233 --> 00:33:49,110
AND?

637
00:33:49,152 --> 00:33:52,447
SAFE TO SAY I KNOW WHERE
YOU STAND ON THE SUBJECT.

638
00:33:52,489 --> 00:33:55,283
EVEN IF YOU GIVE THEM
OUR REACTOR SCHEMATICS,

639
00:33:55,325 --> 00:33:58,203
THEY DON'T HAVE
THE TECHNICAL EXPERTISE

640
00:33:58,244 --> 00:34:00,998
TO BUILD A WARP ENGINE.

641
00:34:01,039 --> 00:34:04,626
THEY HAVE NO EXPERIENCE
WORKING WITH ANTIMATTER.

642
00:34:04,668 --> 00:34:08,547
I DOUBT THEY EVEN REALIZE
HOW DANGEROUS IT IS.

643
00:34:10,841 --> 00:34:12,342
THEY'RE NOT READY.

644
00:34:12,384 --> 00:34:17,347
T'POL: THEN YOUR DECISION
SHOULDN'T BE DIFFICULT.

645
00:34:17,389 --> 00:34:20,308
WE COULD...

646
00:34:20,350 --> 00:34:23,645
STAY AND HELP THEM.

647
00:34:23,687 --> 00:34:27,232
THE VULCANS STAYED
TO HELP EARTH 90 YEARS AGO.

648
00:34:27,273 --> 00:34:30,318
WE'RE STILL THERE.

649
00:34:33,655 --> 00:34:36,157
I NEVER THOUGHT
I'D SAY THIS, BUT...

650
00:34:36,199 --> 00:34:42,163
I'M BEGINNING TO UNDERSTAND HOW
THE VULCANS MUST HAVE FELT.

651
00:35:11,651 --> 00:35:13,070
[ DOOR OPENS ]

652
00:35:15,530 --> 00:35:17,532
TROUBLE SLEEPING, CAPTAIN?

653
00:35:17,574 --> 00:35:19,785
ARCHER: LOOKS LIKE
I'M NOT THE ONLY ONE.

654
00:35:19,826 --> 00:35:21,954
[ CHUCKLES ] ACTUALLY,

655
00:35:21,995 --> 00:35:26,583
DENOBULANS
REQUIRE VERY LITTLE REST --

656
00:35:26,625 --> 00:35:29,252
UNLESS YOU COUNT
OUR ANNUAL HIBERNATION CYCLE.

657
00:35:29,294 --> 00:35:33,131
AM I GOING TO BE WITHOUT
MY DOCTOR THIS WINTER?

658
00:35:33,172 --> 00:35:34,466
ONLY FOR SIX DAYS.

659
00:35:34,507 --> 00:35:37,510
[ Chuckling ]
MAYBE I'LL JOIN YOU.

660
00:35:39,345 --> 00:35:41,723
ANY PROGRESS?

661
00:35:44,810 --> 00:35:49,230
THE RESEARCH HAS BEEN
CHALLENGING, TO SAY THE LEAST.

662
00:35:49,272 --> 00:35:51,316
A CURE, DOCTOR...

663
00:35:51,357 --> 00:35:53,526
HAVE YOU FOUND A CURE?

664
00:35:59,992 --> 00:36:02,911
EVEN IF I COULD FIND ONE,

665
00:36:02,953 --> 00:36:05,330
I'M NOT SURE
IT WOULD BE ETHICAL.

666
00:36:05,371 --> 00:36:06,999
ETHICAL?

667
00:36:07,040 --> 00:36:09,626
WE'D BE INTERFERING WITH
AN EVOLUTIONARY PROCESS

668
00:36:09,668 --> 00:36:14,297
THAT HAS BEEN GOING ON
FOR THOUSANDS OF YEARS.

669
00:36:14,339 --> 00:36:16,466
EVERY TIME YOU
TREAT AN ILLNESS,

670
00:36:16,508 --> 00:36:18,259
YOU'RE INTERFERING.

671
00:36:18,301 --> 00:36:19,928
THAT'S WHAT DOCTORS DO.

672
00:36:19,970 --> 00:36:23,348
YOU'RE FORGETTING
ABOUT THE MENK.

673
00:36:23,389 --> 00:36:25,558
WHAT ABOUT THE MENK?

674
00:36:25,600 --> 00:36:28,770
I'VE BEEN STUDYING
THEIR GENOME, AS WELL,

675
00:36:28,812 --> 00:36:31,148
AND I'VE SEEN EVIDENCE
OF INCREASING INTELLIGENCE,

676
00:36:31,189 --> 00:36:33,525
MOTOR SKILLS,
LINGUISTIC ABILITIES.

677
00:36:33,566 --> 00:36:34,734
UNLIKE THE VALAKIANS,

678
00:36:34,776 --> 00:36:36,319
THEY APPEAR TO BE
IN THE PROCESS

679
00:36:36,361 --> 00:36:38,613
OF AN EVOLUTIONARY
AWAKENING.

680
00:36:38,655 --> 00:36:41,574
IT MAY TAKE MILLENNIA,

681
00:36:41,616 --> 00:36:43,201
BUT THE MENK HAVE THE POTENTIAL

682
00:36:43,242 --> 00:36:45,829
TO BECOME THE DOMINANT SPECIES
ON THIS PLANET.

683
00:36:45,871 --> 00:36:48,123
AND THAT WON'T HAPPEN

684
00:36:48,165 --> 00:36:50,959
AS LONG AS THE VALAKIANS
ARE AROUND.

685
00:36:51,001 --> 00:36:53,545
IF THE MENK ARE TO FLOURISH,

686
00:36:53,586 --> 00:36:56,381
THEY NEED AN OPPORTUNITY
TO SURVIVE ON THEIR OWN.

687
00:36:56,422 --> 00:36:59,134
NOW WHAT ARE YOU SUGGESTING?

688
00:36:59,176 --> 00:37:04,890
WE CHOOSE ONE SPECIES
OVER THE OTHER?

689
00:37:04,931 --> 00:37:09,394
ALL I'M SAYING IS THAT WE
LET NATURE MAKE THE CHOICE.

690
00:37:09,435 --> 00:37:11,229
THE HELL WITH NATURE.

691
00:37:11,270 --> 00:37:12,438
YOU'RE A DOCTOR.

692
00:37:12,480 --> 00:37:13,857
YOU HAVE A MORAL OBLIGATION

693
00:37:13,899 --> 00:37:15,775
TO HELP PEOPLE
WHO ARE SUFFERING.

694
00:37:15,817 --> 00:37:17,318
I'M ALSO A SCIENTIST,

695
00:37:17,360 --> 00:37:20,446
AND I'M OBLIGATED TO CONSIDER
THE LARGER ISSUES.

696
00:37:20,488 --> 00:37:23,324
35,000 YEARS AGO,
YOUR SPECIES

697
00:37:23,366 --> 00:37:25,911
COEXISTED WITH OTHER HUMANOIDS,
ISN'T THAT CORRECT?

698
00:37:25,952 --> 00:37:27,913
[ SIGHS ] GO AHEAD.

699
00:37:27,954 --> 00:37:31,332
WHAT IF AN ALIEN RACE
HAD INTERFERED

700
00:37:31,374 --> 00:37:35,628
AND GIVEN THE NEANDERTHALS
AN EVOLUTIONARY ADVANTAGE?

701
00:37:35,670 --> 00:37:37,380
FORTUNATELY FOR YOU,
THEY DIDN'T.

702
00:37:37,422 --> 00:37:40,842
I APPRECIATE YOUR PERSPECTIVE
ON ALL OF THIS.

703
00:37:40,884 --> 00:37:44,345
BUT WE'RE TALKING ABOUT
SOMETHING THAT MIGHT HAPPEN...

704
00:37:44,387 --> 00:37:46,139
<i>MIGHT</i> HAPPEN...

705
00:37:46,181 --> 00:37:48,725
THOUSANDS OF YEARS FROM NOW.

706
00:37:48,767 --> 00:37:52,395
THEY'VE ASKED FOR OUR HELP.

707
00:37:52,437 --> 00:37:56,816
I AM NOT PREPARED TO WALK AWAY
BASED ON A THEORY.

708
00:37:56,858 --> 00:37:59,402
EVOLUTION IS MORE THAN A THEORY.

709
00:37:59,444 --> 00:38:01,487
IT IS A FUNDAMENTAL
SCIENTIFIC PRINCIPLE.

710
00:38:01,529 --> 00:38:03,406
FORGIVE ME FOR SAYING SO...

711
00:38:03,448 --> 00:38:05,825
BUT I BELIEVE YOUR COMPASSION
FOR THESE PEOPLE

712
00:38:05,867 --> 00:38:07,202
IS AFFECTING YOUR JUDGMENT.

713
00:38:07,244 --> 00:38:09,621
MY COMPASSION
GUIDES MY JUDGMENT.

714
00:38:09,662 --> 00:38:10,872
CAPTAIN...

715
00:38:10,914 --> 00:38:13,250
ARCHER: CAN YOU FIND A CURE?

716
00:38:15,501 --> 00:38:17,921
DOCTOR?

717
00:38:26,221 --> 00:38:27,973
I ALREADY HAVE.

718
00:38:30,809 --> 00:38:32,144
PHLOX:<i> TWO DAYS AGO,</i>

719
00:38:32,185 --> 00:38:34,646
<i>WHEN WE FIRST DISCOVERED</i>
<i>THE ALIEN SHUTTLE,</i>

720
00:38:34,687 --> 00:38:36,773
<i>I HAD NO IDEA</i>
<i>THAT I'D BE FACING A DILEMMA</i>

721
00:38:36,815 --> 00:38:38,691
<i>OF THIS MAGNITUDE.</i>

722
00:38:38,733 --> 00:38:41,153
<i>FOR THE FIRST TIME,</i>
<i>I FIND MYSELF IN CONFLICT</i>

723
00:38:41,194 --> 00:38:42,612
<i>WITH MY CAPTAIN.</i>

724
00:38:42,654 --> 00:38:46,032
<i>BUT HE</i> IS<i> MY CAPTAIN,</i>

725
00:38:46,074 --> 00:38:48,451
<i>AND HE'S PLACED A GREAT DEAL</i>
<i>OF TRUST IN ME.</i>

726
00:38:48,493 --> 00:38:50,662
<i>I BELIEVE I OWE HIM THE SAME.</i>

727
00:38:50,703 --> 00:38:52,247
<i>I ONLY HOPE THAT HE IS WILLING</i>

728
00:38:52,289 --> 00:38:55,750
<i>TO LOOK BEYOND HIS SYMPATHY</i>
<i>FOR THESE POOR PEOPLE.</i>

729
00:38:55,792 --> 00:38:58,044
[ DOOR OPENS ]

730
00:39:03,424 --> 00:39:05,302
DOCTOR.

731
00:39:05,343 --> 00:39:06,845
CAPTAIN.

732
00:39:08,554 --> 00:39:10,182
I'M...

733
00:39:10,223 --> 00:39:13,518
GOING DOWN TO
THE VALAKIAN HOSPITAL.

734
00:39:13,559 --> 00:39:16,313
SIR...

735
00:39:16,354 --> 00:39:18,190
IT WOULD GO AGAINST
ALL MY PRINCIPLES

736
00:39:18,231 --> 00:39:19,565
IF I DIDN'T ASK YOU
TO RECONSIDER --

737
00:39:19,607 --> 00:39:22,235
I<i> HAVE</i> RECONSIDERED.

738
00:39:22,277 --> 00:39:25,905
I SPENT THE WHOLE NIGHT
RECONSIDERING.

739
00:39:25,947 --> 00:39:29,742
AND WHAT I'VE DECIDED
GOES AGAINST ALL<i> MY</i> PRINCIPLES.

740
00:39:33,496 --> 00:39:37,709
SOMEDAY, MY PEOPLE
ARE GOING TO COME UP WITH

741
00:39:37,750 --> 00:39:39,460
SOME SORT OF A DOCTRINE,

742
00:39:39,502 --> 00:39:43,215
SOMETHING THAT TELLS US WHAT
WE CAN AND CAN'T DO OUT HERE,

743
00:39:43,256 --> 00:39:46,467
SHOULD AND SHOULDN'T DO.

744
00:39:46,509 --> 00:39:53,099
BUT UNTIL SOMEBODY TELLS ME THAT
THEY'VE DRAFTED THAT DIRECTIVE,

745
00:39:53,141 --> 00:39:58,146
I'M GOING TO HAVE TO REMIND
MYSELF EVERY DAY

746
00:39:58,188 --> 00:40:02,734
THAT WE DIDN'T COME OUT HERE
TO PLAY GOD.

747
00:40:02,775 --> 00:40:05,278
PHLOX:<i> I'D LIKE TO THINK,</i>
<i>DR. LUCAS,</i>

748
00:40:05,320 --> 00:40:08,156
<i>THAT IF I HAD A CHANCE</i>
<i>TO TALK TO YOU FACE-TO-FACE,</i>

749
00:40:08,198 --> 00:40:09,824
<i>YOU'D HAVE NEVER LET ME</i>
<i>EVEN CONSIDER</i>

750
00:40:09,866 --> 00:40:12,327
<i>WITHHOLDING MY FINDINGS</i>
<i>FROM THE CAPTAIN.</i>

751
00:40:12,369 --> 00:40:17,916
<i>BUT I'M ASHAMED TO SAY,</i>
<i>I ALMOST DID JUST THAT.</i>

752
00:40:17,957 --> 00:40:24,672
PHLOX TELLS ME THIS MEDICINE
WILL HELP EASE THE SYMPTOMS...

753
00:40:24,714 --> 00:40:27,633
FOR A DECADE, MAYBE MORE.

754
00:40:30,011 --> 00:40:33,181
A LOT CAN HAPPEN IN THAT TIME.

755
00:40:33,223 --> 00:40:36,935
I WOULDN'T BE SURPRISED IF YOU
DEVELOPED A CURE ON YOUR OWN.

756
00:40:36,976 --> 00:40:38,978
AND IF WE DON'T?

757
00:40:41,273 --> 00:40:43,066
WITH A WARP-CAPABLE STARSHIP,

758
00:40:43,108 --> 00:40:46,403
OUR CHANCES WOULD BE
GREATLY IMPROVED.

759
00:40:53,451 --> 00:40:56,037
I'M SORRY.

760
00:40:58,664 --> 00:41:01,793
THIS WILL GIVE YOU

761
00:41:01,834 --> 00:41:03,044
DETAILED INSTRUCTIONS

762
00:41:03,086 --> 00:41:08,007
ON HOW TO SYNTHESIZE
MORE OF THE MEDICINE.

763
00:41:08,049 --> 00:41:11,886
WE APPRECIATE
EVERYTHING YOU'VE DONE.

764
00:41:14,513 --> 00:41:17,683
PHLOX:<i> IF I HADN'T TRUSTED HIM</i>
<i>TO MAKE THE RIGHT CHOICE,</i>

765
00:41:17,725 --> 00:41:20,145
<i>I'D HAVE BEEN NO BETTER</i>
<i>THAN THE VULCAN DIPLOMATS</i>

766
00:41:20,186 --> 00:41:23,273
<i>WHO HELD YOUR SPECIES BACK</i>
<i>BECAUSE THEY FELT</i>

767
00:41:23,315 --> 00:41:26,401
<i>YOU COULDN'T MAKE</i>
<i>PROPER DECISIONS ON YOUR OWN.</i>

768
00:41:26,443 --> 00:41:31,448
I CAME VERY CLOSE
TO MISJUDGING JONATHAN ARCHER.

769
00:41:31,489 --> 00:41:37,495
BUT THIS INCIDENT HAS HELPED ME
GAIN A NEW RESPECT FOR HIM.

770
00:41:37,536 --> 00:41:40,832
HAPPINESS AND HEALTH TO YOU,
DOCTOR.

771
00:41:40,873 --> 00:41:46,296
YOUR, UH...
DEDICATED COLLEAGUE, PHLOX.

772
00:41:49,715 --> 00:41:52,593
YOU WANTED TO SEE ME?

773
00:41:52,635 --> 00:41:55,680
PLEASE.

774
00:41:55,721 --> 00:41:58,266
FOR DR. LUCAS.

775
00:41:58,308 --> 00:42:02,020
IT'LL GO OUT FIRST THING
IN THE MORNING.

776
00:42:02,061 --> 00:42:04,689
EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

777
00:42:04,730 --> 00:42:07,900
FINE. FINE.

778
00:42:07,942 --> 00:42:12,447
THE PAST FEW DAYS
HAVE BEEN...TAXING.

779
00:42:12,489 --> 00:42:15,616
WANT MY ADVICE?

780
00:42:15,658 --> 00:42:17,702
GET OUT OF SICK BAY.

781
00:42:17,743 --> 00:42:20,246
YES.

782
00:42:20,288 --> 00:42:21,706
PERHAPS YOU'RE RIGHT.

783
00:42:21,747 --> 00:42:25,001
GOOD NIGHT.

784
00:42:26,044 --> 00:42:28,087
GOOD NIGHT.

785
00:42:36,804 --> 00:42:38,890
[ BEEP ]

786
00:42:38,931 --> 00:42:41,726
PHLOX TO CREWMAN CUTLER.

787
00:42:41,767 --> 00:42:43,353
CUTLER: Go ahead.

788
00:42:43,395 --> 00:42:47,232
I, UH, KNOW
IT'S SHORT NOTICE, BUT...

789
00:42:47,273 --> 00:42:49,317
I WAS WONDERING IF YOU MIGHT
LIKE TO JOIN ME

790
00:42:49,359 --> 00:42:53,321
FOR A LITTLE SNACK
IN THE MESS HALL.

791
00:42:53,363 --> 00:42:58,659
I COULD USE A, UH,
A FRIEND RIGHT ABOUT NOW.

792
00:42:58,701 --> 00:43:00,453
CUTLER: 10 minutes?

793
00:43:00,495 --> 00:43:01,913
THANK YOU.

794
00:43:01,954 --> 00:43:04,165
[ BEEP ]

795
00:43:14,050 --> 00:43:15,843
SWEET DREAMS.
